\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\emph on
Schwartz space
\emph default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{S}\left(\mathbb{R}^{n}\right)$
\end_inset

 is the vector space of all 
\begin_inset Formula $f\in C^{\infty}\left(\mathbb{R}^{n}\right)$
\end_inset

 for which all Schwartz norms are finite, i.e.
 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $r,s\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

 holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\norm f_{r,s} & <\infty
\end{align*}

\end_inset

This space is an infinite-dimensional vector space.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

On a normed space 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(E,\norm .\right)$
\end_inset

, the topology is given by the open sets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega\subseteq E$
\end_inset

 is defined as 
\emph on
open
\emph default
 if holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\fall_{x\in\Omega}\ \exs_{\varepsilon>0}\ :\ B_{\varepsilon}\left(x\right) & \subseteq\Omega
\end{align*}

\end_inset

A subset 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega\subseteq\mathcal{S}\left(\mathbb{R}^{n}\right)$
\end_inset

